..listen, buddy, I don't know who you are or what kind of raiding you do. Me, I'm a mythic raider in a world top 10 guild. I don't care what kind of class we're talking about, or which role you play, or how many days or how many raids a week, everyone falls into one of those two categories. The raiders who are not competitors? They'll back off if it's starting to get uncomfortable. Why? Because they have no reason to push themselves that hard. In terms of progress, if they push past normal and into heroic or beyond, they won't stay there for more than a very short amount of time before backing off, because it's uncomfortable for them, and they don't feel the need to go that far.

Mythic raiders? They aren't pushing themselves to the point of it being abject suffering for no good reason, they know that on the other side of that suffering, there are gains.
